oh dear

12 years ago, you changed my life when i walked into your office at 14 years old… it wasn’t even a formal meeting, but that night you called and told me that you believed in me so much that i needed to move to Los Angeles… and you would be my manager. And so because of you, my whole family did. All because you gave them the validation that my crazy big ambitious dreams were something worth believing in. 

Through every twist and turn my life has taken since then, you never once stopped believing in me. When I told you I was gay, you were so excited and went above and beyond to find projects with characters for me to go out for that I could relate to, bc you knew how important that was to me. You came to graduations, performances, events, and always looked at me with pride - and i never ever took that for granted. no matter how low i was, or in moments where i struggled to believe in myself - you were always there to tell me to fix my posture 😂, and keep going.

I am in shock, and beyond broken by this news. but i feel so grateful to have known you, and honored to have been a part of the community of incredible artists you welcomed with open arms and that big fabulous smile into your @discovermgmt family.

i will miss you terribly, DebraLynn. thank you for being the best manager to that little boy i used to be, and the man I grew to be today. Rest in peace. 🤍🤍🤍🤍🤍🤍

feeling more like myself again. 🫶🏼

this month has been… tough on the mental, to say the least. ive always been someone who puts a lot of pressure on myself to show up for everyone. always. even at the expense of myself, in fear that people would think poorly of me if i appear to put my needs in front of theirs.

but sometimes, you have to! it’s okay to take a step back and evaluate how much emotional energy you’re giving to yourself vs. other people and respectfully reroute with grace.

i don’t need to explain myself - and im awful at asking for help when i need it. i just felt like sharing a sliver of what ive been going through because it feels like a lot of people around me seem to be struggling with their anxieties and insecurities too, and it’s okay.

sending you all love & light, and if you actually cared to read this TED talk of a rant - thanks for your time. xx
